data.raw: Dear all, We need five graduate student volunteers AND five undergraduate student volunteers to help with our annual ACM-ICPC programming REGIONAL contest. This year we have a total of 21 teams participating at our site from around the region. Perk Volunteers will get a T-shirt and food and a LOT of satisfaction. Date needed: Saturday November 3rd. Work Time Several hours between 8am and 5pm. If interested, just reply to this email (BY NEXT Tuesday Many Thanks, Simanta
data.subject: ACM ICPC Regional Volunteers needed (both Grads and Undergrads)

data.raw: Welcome Engineering Students! Quick Guide to Engineering Information Technology Resources Computer Lab information Want to know where the Engineering labs are? Want to see if a lab has open seats before walking around campu Visit our site at Keep Your Computer Labs Clean! Take pride in your computer labs! Please pickup after yourself and keep the labs clean for you and everyone else. As always, there is NO FOOD OR DRINK allowed in computer lab Lost and Found If you lose an item in one of the computer labs or need to turn in a lost item, please visit one of our Lost and Found location 2071 Black Engineering, 2215 Coover Hall, 2240 Hoover Hall, and 1200 Howe Hall. Remember to write your name on calculators and other items of value so they can be easily identified if lost. We will require proof before returning lost item Printing As an Engineering student you receive 4,000 print units per semester. Black and white printing is 5 units per side and color is 15 units per side. Lab computers automatically have local printers added. You are also able to print from a personal computer using Papercut Web Print or Google Print. Please visit and for detail Remote Acce Many of the applications available in the computer labs are also available remotely using your own computer. Please visit for more details and instructions on how to connect. CyBox ISU offers all students unlimited storage through a partnership with called CyBox. Visit for detail Personal Drive Please note it is limited to 10 GB. Microsoft Office and Engineering applications for FREE! For a list of titles, visit our IT portal at Departmental Specific Resources Did you know each major has their own dedicated IT staff? Check with your departmental IT staff for information about unique resources available to your major. Other Question All this information and more can be found at . If you have any other questions, please fill out our contact form located at Please remember when contacting us that your ISU e-mail addre is the most important piece of information we need about you. Your University ID (9-digit number) is not needed. Distributed by Engineering Technology Support. Copyright © 2018, Iowa State University of Science and Technology. All rights reserved. data.raw: September Undergraduate Newsletter Curriculum Corner Welcome back from all of us in Student Services! We are trying to meet as many of you as possible in the first 10 days of classes to make sure everything is set for your semester! If it is like the summer—it will whiz by! 1) Please note that we will be celebrating Scholars’ Fair on Tuesday, Sept. 11, from 5:30 p.m. – 7 p.m. Please join us in the excitement of student organization membership, faculty and grad student research and lots of giveaway 2) Welcome Dr Mai Zheng and Mohamed Selim as new computer engineering faculty members! You’ll probably see them in the hallways of Coover. 3) Remember that appointments can be made on AccessPlus . 4) As you think of spring semester, we will be teaching EE 439, EE 425x and Cpr E/EE 503X (see the experimental course list 5) If you are still looking for a part-time job, Vicky is trying to find an undergrad TAs for Engr 160, Cpr E 381, EE/Cpr E 294 and 394 Undergraduate Circuit First FAN Club meeting of the year, 9/28 - FREE PIZZA!!! Want to be a part of something more Join one of our student orgs! From solar decatholons to engineering ambassadors, we have so much for you!! Click here to see all our student organization  Don't forget about all of our opportunities to better your chances of scoring a job at the career fair! Study Abroad Fair, Tuesday, Sept. 4 - Come and see ALL the places YOU can study in around the WORLD! Summer Sparks Check out some of the research and moments that happened over this summer!!
